{"name": "markdown-captions", "metadata": {"name": "markdown-captions", "version": "2.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Markup :: HTML"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Evidlo/markdown_captions", "license": "GPL3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Turn markdown images into captioned images using <figure>", "upload_time": 1658269768}, "documentation": ["# markdown-captions\n\nConverts images with alt text to `<figure>` with `<figcaption>`.\n\n## Usage\n\n```\npip install markdown-captions\n```\n\n``` python\nmd = markdown.Markdown(\n    extensions=[\n        'markdown_captions',\n        'attr_list' # optional\n    ]\n)\n```\n\n## Examples\n\nsimple example\n``` md\n![caption](img.jpg)\n![caption2](img2.jpg)\n```\n``` html\n<p>\n  <figure><img src=\"img.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption</figcaption></figure>\n  <figure><img src=\"img2.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption2</figcaption></figure>\n</p>\n```\n\nimage title and class (with attr_list extension)\n``` md\n![caption](img.jpg \"title\"){: .class1 }\n```\n``` html\n<figure class=\"class1\"><img src=\"img.jpg\" title=\"title\" /><figcaption>caption</figcaption></figure>\n```\n\ninline captioned images\n``` md\n<style>\n    .inline {\n        display: inline-block;\n    }\n</style>\n![caption](img.jpg){: .inline }\n![caption2](img2.jpg){: .inline }\n```\n``` html\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"inline\"><img src=\"img.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption</figcaption></figure>\n  <figure class=\"inline\"><img src=\"img2.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption2</figcaption></figure>\n</p>\n```\n\nimages with no alt text are not captioned\n``` md\n![](img.jpg)\n```\n``` html\n<img src=\"img.jpg\" />\n```\n\nreferenced images, and shorthand references are also supported\n\n``` md\n![caption][ref]\n![caption2]\n\n[ref]: img.jpg\n[caption2]: img2.jpg\n```\n\n``` html\n<p>\n  <figure><img src=\"img.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption</figcaption></figure>\n  <figure><img src=\"img2.jpg\" /><figcaption>caption2</figcaption></figure>\n</p>\n```\n\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "markdown_captions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "markdown_captions.CaptionsExtension", "xref": {"fqname": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.CaptionsExtension", "project": null}}, {"name": "markdown_captions.makeExtension", "xref": {"fqname": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.makeExtension", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions", "documentation": ["Evan Widloski - 2019-04-18", "python-markdown extension for captions"], "functions": [{"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.makeExtension", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.CAPTION_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.ImageInlineProcessor", "bases": ["LinkInlineProcessor"], "methods": [{"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.ImageInlineProcessor.handleMatch", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "m", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["handle regular inline image: ![caption](img.jpg)"]}, {"name": "markdown_captions.markdown_captions.ImageReferenceInlineProcessor", "bases": ["ReferenceInlineProcessor"], "methods": [{"name": "markdown_captions.markdow